cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a design of memory augmented neural networks (MANNs) for classification tasks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of memory in the network also relates to natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper demonstrates the effectiveness of the proposed method on word-modelling and few-shot learning tasks, which are commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) subfields.
